OL,3,C#5 billion welfare cuts needed to
OL,4,C'save' system, Kendall to say
OL,6,FIn a separate, earlier letter, 42 MPs
OL,7,Fsaid the cuts were "impossible to
OL,8,Fsupport".
OL,10,FRachel Reeves's local Labour party,
OL,11,FLeeds West and Pudsey Constituency
OL,12,FLabour Party (CLP), has, meanwhile,
OL,13,Fagreed to write to the Chancellor
OL,14,Fvoicing its opposition to the cuts.
OL,16,FIn a motion seen by the PA news
OL,17,Fagency, the CLP said disabled people
OL,18,F"are not responsible for the state of
OL,19,Fthe national finances and should not
OL,20,Fbe made to pay the price for Tory
OL,21,Feconomic mismanagement".
